<h3>Process</h3>

<p>As you might expect with UX work like this, I spent the biggest share of time understanding the problem through usability testing, interviews, contextual inquiry, and analyzing data from search. We went through this process over the course of 4 months from project start to launch.   
</p>

<p>We discovered that students and parents were overwhelmed and confused by the information they found on the financial aid department’s website. There was not a simple explanation of the process, a list of items needed before starting the application, or even a list of minimal requirements for qualification. As a result, many applications were considered “incomplete” by the office; their policy did not allow for processing of incomplete applications, so users ended up having to stand in line at the financial aid office again and again. To make matters worse, we learned that the aid office was so busy that they limited the amount of hours they answered phone calls in order to process applications. You can imagine the lines of anxious, unhappy students and parents unable to get basic questions answered.</p>

